parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel System Failure - Stalling after Refueling
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of power steering and braking, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded in traffic.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or hesitates after refueling
often within a mile or less of driving
and may exhibit bucking or surging. The steering wheel may lock up
and the vehicle may experience a loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel tank rollover valve can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power steering and brakes, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The engine stalls after filling up the fuel tank

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front suspension can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents and injuries.
